Pyro README File
----------------

Information for the Python Robotics system

1. INSTALL

To use Pyro, you will need all of the following installed:

* Python 2.0, or greater
* Python Numeric module
* Python module PyOpenGL 

Briefly:

0. su -
1. tar xfz Numeric-20.3.tar.gz
2. cd Numeric-20.3
3. python2.1 setup.py install
4. cd 
5. tar xfz PyOpenGL-2.0.0.44.tar.g
6. cd PyOpenGL-2.0.0.44
7. python2.1 setup.py build
8. python2.1 setup.py install

Pyro has been tested on RedHat Linux, 7.2.

Once the above have been installed, you are ready to setup the
environment and make the Pyro C-based modules. 

First, put the tar file where you will install the system:

% mv pyro-X.X.tgz /usr/local/
% cd /usr/local

Untar the system:

% tar xfz pyro-X.X.tgz

Setup up the PYRO environment variable, for example:

% cd pyro
% export PYRO=/usr/local/pyro

To set up other environment variables:

% . bin/environment.sh

Next, change to the pyro subdirectory, and make the system:

% cd $PYRO
% make all

2. GETTING STARTED

You start Pyro with the command:

% $PYRO/bin/pyro

or put $PYRO/bin in your path and just call pyro.

In the startup window
